Mike-

I believe the First Data Rapid Connect certification will be completed next week.? After that, the
outstanding certifications would include TSYS, Heartland, and Chase Paymentech.

From a functionality perspective, we still have several outstanding items:
1. ?Manual Card Entry ? This is part of "fallback" processing, so if their device isn't working and
they resort to keying a transaction, the transaction fails.? Randy confirmed this also fails when
processing through your UTG platform.
2. ?Auto Decryption of Ingenico and Verifone devices ? We use a different type of encryption
called "voltage" encryption that will force a re-encryption when a transaction routes through the
4Go (or UTG) platform.? This is also causing transactions to fail if the device isn't encrypted
with one of First Data's formats.
3. ?Dealer parameter is only working for Elavon, not First Data.? As a reminder, all billing,
statements, and reporting are pulled from this Dealer code.?

We're continuing to work with First Data to determine if there are any solutions to the issues
above or if we have to approach this project from a different angle.? In addition, we're working
with Nate on next steps and options.

Thanks,
J.R.

Mike-

I believe the First Data Rapid Connect certification will be completed next week.  After that, the
outstanding certifications would include TSYS, Heartland, and Chase Paymentech.

From a functionality perspective, we still have several outstanding items:
1. Manual Card Entry - This is part of "fallback" processing, so if their device isn't working and
they resort to keying a transaction, the transaction fails.  Randy confirmed this also fails when
processing through your UTG platform.
2. Auto Decryption of Ingenico and Verifone devices - We use a different type of encryption
called "voltage" encryption that will force a re-encryption when a transaction routes through the
4Go (or UTG) platform.  This is also causing transactions to fail if the device isn't encrypted
with one of First Data's formats.
3. Dealer parameter is only working for Elavon, not First Data.  As a reminder, all billing,
statements, and reporting are pulled from this Dealer code.

We're continuing to work with First Data to determine if there are any solutions to the issues
above or if we have to approach this project from a different angle.  In addition, we're working
with Nate on next steps and options.

Thanks,
J.R.
